<subSubSection id="92189B511D1C1BA10FEDF997D1FF0B90" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="34FB54BDF8B9FE3DF194FCF41C6B5897" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ecology and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FC0F418D2CE6AE366DB9F2A5EA87DAB7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
No habitat notes are recorded on the type gathering of 
<taxonomicName id="6E8A34C11DF537CBA422A48D191C1311" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. putii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="putii">
<emphasis id="46437C97CA60C75E07984EE72799C5F0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. putii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but possibly occurs in dry forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A460FD64E0200E600F2EEBFE8958F643" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="common names and uses">
<paragraph id="808BD0C18AF3EDB397F290E34070BB36" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Common names and uses.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0A1BA088597EB0EF7D5E9492F2FAFCA1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">None recorded.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C69C22B63AFAFC0DC8BC392E31D2EA46" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="preliminary conservation status">
<paragraph id="E94C50F50E7E4295476B59522BAD2D9A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Preliminary conservation status</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B3D4BE251AFB93AF738D3C4E30B506AC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="8ED4E440239883325D52C38303E8189E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
(
<bibRefCitation id="0443E62B13F94562248F7166E45E558D" author="Hutchings, A" journalOrPublisher="AGRIVITA Journal of Agricultural Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" refId="B105" refString="2019. . http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" year="2019">IUCN 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Data Deficient (DD). 
<taxonomicName id="FEB54D3B3BE05CAFAC491D5523A7BA6A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum putii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="putii">
<emphasis id="4ACD7D10674549642B6D8B0F93E9D405" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum putii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from the type collection and little is known about this species otherwise.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EB0EB4FF95F07D589F055D9AB7943B81" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2FCE83FDB7B234BF53FF28A013F04057" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4D903E27271B3E74BFE9D92766604A7F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="9620A2885AB40D5FC9D23B9EDE1F715A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum putii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="putii">
<emphasis id="9FC1454C93043FB1D18263E7DAA9FAF0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum putii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar and may be conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="C4720FDB528A250F875935259F8A688E" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. robinsonii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="robinsonii">
<emphasis id="DCDCBE3200096F9EB4600844BFE6DD20" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. robinsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but we hesitate to synonymise these two taxa until more material is available; the similarities were noted in the original description (notes in packet on holotype at K; 
<bibRefCitation id="0712EE9139638F9AF806E73D4A90C668" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4114708" author="Barnett, EC" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="485 - 490" refId="B13" refString="Barnett, EC, 1963. Contributions to the Flora of Thailand: LVI: Descriptions of new species from Dr. Kerr's manuscript. Kew Bulletin 16 (3): 485 - 490, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4114708" title="Contributions to the Flora of Thailand: LVI: Descriptions of new species from Dr. Kerr's manuscript." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4114708" volume="16" year="1963">Barnett 1963</bibRefCitation>
). The leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="D3A6DB3013C4BB01F165069AC7985F5F" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. putii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="putii">
<emphasis id="624972858C3A5DE8EC2107A4800BFD2C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. putii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are more broadly elliptic, more softly pubescent, and less discolorous that those of 
<taxonomicName id="CE99F89E85899BAAD2E016A52F70A7B2" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. robinsonii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="robinsonii">
<emphasis id="DC3FD7636A61F9945FCC9711A8BF50BB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. robinsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; they are also markedly oblique at the base, while those of 
<taxonomicName id="2409697E130FDBFB1F745C99C2DC8FC3" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. robinsonii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="robinsonii">
<emphasis id="F0B7AF9452826528CC2F57F33D4EFF96" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. robinsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not. The lamina beneath is clearly visible and the rays on the stellate trichomes are thinner and more delicate. A single dissected flower on the isotype sheet at BM is 7-merous and clearly fascinated, perhaps indicating this is an aberrant plant, a note by Kerr on the holotype at K states &quot;Only flower of 
<emphasis id="C65AFE68A908856B61722A74CE98AF55" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Put 3227</emphasis>
examined was abnormal with double ovary, stamens, etc.&quot;. The fruit of 
<taxonomicName id="0F5DBB94A83E70F2F4DCCB038CF94D3C" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. putii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="putii">
<emphasis id="ACB975E816D5CD4F8E6369B3884B6E51" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. putii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are smaller (ca. 0.6 cm in diameter) than those of 
<taxonomicName id="F552156DD9DF52247A53291C95779BA7" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. robinsonii" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="robinsonii">
<emphasis id="C5D62501B89BFDA90AEACE92027DAD7B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. robinsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(ca. 1 cm in diameter).
</paragraph>
